~ launch
=>< snippets/focus_forward
[next=2]
do set_journey_progress(0.2,16.0)
[next=12]

~ were_flying
do Character.play_audio("were_flying")
Sam: We’re flying![next=5]

~ skip_to_warp
System: Debug Selection.
- Continue
- Skip to Warp 'task2_stimuli'
	do overlay_state("hidden")
	=> task2_stimuli

~ task1_intro
[next=4]
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
do Character.play_audio("task1_intro")
Sam: Boy, it’s dark out here! This time, let’s wake up the stars with our voices. Our super computer has a list of all the stars’ favourite phrases to hear! If we listen to the computer and repeat the special phrases loud and clear, the stars will wake up. After each phrase, I’ll press the red button to tell the computer to send your voice to the stars.  
=>< snippets/focus_forward

~ task1_stimuli_order
System: Select stimuli order
- Order A
	=>< orders/A
- Order B
	=>< orders/B
- Order C
	=>< orders/C
- Order D
	=>< orders/D
- Skip to success. 
	=> task1_success

~ task1_stimuli_trial
# loop through stimuli
while stimuli_set.size() > 0
	set next_stimuli = stimuli_set.pop_front()
#	do get_next_stimuli()
	System:
	- Begin {{next_stimuli}}
	do print_message("Step: %s" % (12 - stimuli_set.size()))

	set screen = "computer"
	do Stimuli.play(next_stimuli)
	do Recorder.start()
	[next=2]
	set screen = "recording"
	[next=3]
	System:
	- Success
		set screen = "success"
		do Recorder.stop()
		do Recorder.save()
		do move_star(stimuli_set.size(), 1, 5.0)
		do set_stars_brightness(12 - stimuli_set.size(), 12)
		[next=4]
	- Failure
		set screen = "failure"
		do Recorder.stop()
#		add the stimuli back into the front of the set so it can be repeated
		do stimuli_set.push_front(next_stimuli)
	[next=1]

~ task1_success
do set_journey_progress(0.35,4.0)
=>< snippets/focus_screen
do Character.play_audio("task1_success")
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
Sam: Awesome job, partner! Look at all the bright things you put in space! Now let’s go to Planet Stardust, press the GO button to get closer to finding Lucky! [next=8]
=>< snippets/prompt_green_button
do set_journey_progress(0.5,4.0)
set screen = "idle"
[next=2]



~ task2_intro
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
do Character.play_audio("task2_intro")
Sam: Our next task is to find Planet Stardust! To help us get to Planet Stardust, we’ll need the help of the Command Centre to steer our ship. Like before, you’ll listen to the computer and repeat each special phrase with your voice loud and clear! The computer will send your voice to the Command Centre to steer our ship. [next=15]


~ task2_bad_example
do Character.play_audio("task2_command_center")
Sam: The Command Centre is very picky and will only guide us if you repeat the computer’s special phrases in EXACTLY the same way you heard them. Let’s hear an example of a space cadet not repeating the command right. [next=12]
do Character.play_audio("click_the_red_button_to_hear_it")
Sam: Click the RED button to hear it. [next=2]
=>< snippets/prompt_red_button
do Stimuli.play("example_bad")
[next=4]
do Character.play_audio("oh_no_did_you_hear_that")
set screen = "failure"
Sam: Oh no, did you hear that? [next=2.5]
=>< snippets/focus_conversation


~ task2_bad_example_repeat
do Character.play_audio("task2_bad_example")
Sam: That space cadet didn’t do the best job of repeating EXACTLY what they heard. Let’s hear it again to see where they went wrong! Press the red button again. [next=6]
=>< snippets/focus_screen
=>< snippets/prompt_red_button
do Stimuli.play("example_bad")
[next=4]
do Character.play_audio("task2_bad_example_high_lows")
set screen = "failure"
Sam: Did you hear that? The space cadet said the right words, but didn’t copy the ^highs^ and ~lows~ of the voice. [next=5]



~ task2_good_example
do Character.play_audio("task2_good_example")
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
Sam: For the Command Centre to move our ship, we have to repeat the words in the exact same way we hear them.   Let’s make sure we do a better job. Click the green button to hear a space cadet repeating it back exactly right. [next=9]
=>< snippets/focus_screen
=>< snippets/prompt_green_button
do Stimuli.play("example_good")
[next=4]

set screen = "success"
[next=2]
set screen = "idle"
do Character.play_audio("task2_example_again")
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
Sam: That time, the space cadet did a great job of repeating the words AND the ^highs^ and ~lows~ of the voice. Click the green button to hear the example again. 
=>< snippets/focus_screen
=>< snippets/prompt_green_button
do Stimuli.play("example_good")
set screen = "playing"
[next=4]
set screen = "idle"


~ task2_ready_or_repeat
do Character.play_audio("task2_ready_or_repeat")
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
Sam: Perfect! Are you ready to communicate with the Command Centre to move our ship to Planet Stardust? Remember, we have to move our voice high and low just like the special phrase to steer our ship. Let your Flight Engineer know if you are ready or if you would like to hear the examples again. [next=10]
# experimenter will decide if participant needs to loop back to 1st bad imitation example

System: ...
- Ready
	set screen = "success"
- Repeat
	=> task2_bad_example


~ task2_ready_to_go
do Character.play_audio("task2_ready_to_go")
=>< snippets/focus_conversation
Sam: OK, here we go! Remember that the Command Centre is very sensitive, so repeat what the computer says exactly. Once you repeat after the computer, I’ll click the GREEN button to send the directions to the Command Centre and we can see if our ship moves! I’ll have a seat and let you take control! [next=12]

~ task2_stimuli
#12 Phrases – 6 song, 6 speech randomized (see list of sentences on last page)*
System: Select stimuli order
- Order A
	=>< orders/A
- Order B
	=>< orders/B
- Order C
	=>< orders/C
- Order D
	=>< orders/D
- Skip to success. 
	=> task2_success

~ task2_stimuli_trial
# loop through stimuli
while stimuli_set.size() > 0
	do get_next_stimuli()
	System:
	- Begin {{next_stimuli}}
	set screen = "computer"
	do Stimuli.play(next_stimuli)
	do Recorder.start()
	[next=2]
	set screen = "recording"
	[next=3]
	System:
	- Success
		set screen = "success"
		do Recorder.stop()
		do Recorder.save()
#		make progress
		do set_journey_progress_step(12 - stimuli_set.size(), 12, 3.0)
		[next=4]
	- Failure
		set screen = "failure"
		do Recorder.stop()
#		add the stimuli back into the front of the set so it can be repeated
		do stimuli_set.push_front(next_stimuli)
	[next=1]



